A U.S. senator has revealed he has never sent an email despite completing 12 years in office.

South Carolina Republican Lindsey Graham insisted that he would happily let anyone look at his emails because he had never needed to send one.  

The comments were made on Meet the Press during a discussion about the controversy surrounding Hillary Clinton's use of a private server and personal email account to conduct foreign policy. 

